    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-14T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-14T17:00:00-05:00" n="495"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72112/3729a Suppl.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at London</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-14T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1917—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s May 29, 5 p.m., Prize Court cases.</p>
                <p>Include in report cases in hands of Procurator-General under Order in Council
                    March 11, 1915 which have not been presented to Prize Court.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d495fn1">For order in council of Mar. 11, 1915, see <ref
                            target="frus1915Supp#pg_144">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1915, supp., p.
                        144</ref>.</note> Hasten reply as much as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
